rca of the issue:
Apply button scroll bug RCA — ProgramDetail.jsx uses:
  onClick={() => { navigate('/'); setTimeout(() => document.getElementById('admissions')?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' }), 100); }}
When navigate('/') fires, React unmounts ProgramDetail and mounts Home. Home renders Hero, About, Timeline, Academics first; Admissions appears only after its component tree reconciles. With images/fonts loading the #admissions DOM node is not present at t+100ms, so scrollIntoView silently no-ops. Reproduction: (1) visit /programs/lower-school (2) click program-apply-btn (3) observe URL becomes / but window.scrollY stays ~0. Mitigation: pass navigation state { scrollTo: 'admissions' } and add useEffect in Home reading useLocation().state -> requestAnimationFrame loop or setTimeout 600ms to scroll once the element exists. Alternatively, use Link to='/#admissions' with a hash-aware scroll effect. Applied fix: none (reported to main agent as per fix-scope rules).
